    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The practice of placing soil and turf on the tops of historic walls as a preservation strategy. Traditionally, “hard caps” of cement have been used, but are not as effective in extreme weather, especially harsh frosts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
